i can’t talk a lot about the bulk of my childhood with my mother because i have dissociative amnesia and complex ptsd from it and what i remember is all bad and sad. this woman psychologically tortured me as a form of entertainment and scapegoating because she hated herself.

it was just my biological mother and i from then on, after the divorce, my father an occasional blip on the radar of my childhood, coming and going at the whims of how bad his addiction was that month. they often used me as a pawn in the middle of their arguments still.

my needs and care got lost in the shuffle of my parents eventual divorce. i stopped getting medical care and seeing specialists. my health care was abandoned. i am sure somebody tried to follow up, but things fall through the cracks. there was nobody there to advocate for me.

i am told they were really good parents when i was a baby/toddler. i like to think they did try their best at one time, they just couldn’t handle parenting at all, let alone parenting a chronically ill child with high special needs. they both turned back to addiction.

my parents were addicts who met at alcoholics anonymous, got married quick, got pregnant quick, and had a very premature, very sick baby. they were simply not prepared. it could never excuse all the ways they abused and neglected me. just makes it rly sad for everybody involved.

it’s weird realizing so many things can be true at once, and figuring out how to reconcile them. my biological parents were bad people who abused me but they were also very sick and never had access to resources they needed for their own trauma, mental illness & substance abuse.
